On @realmoney Homes For Sales Multiply in Palm Beach and East Hampton * And my favorite recession "tell" increases the probability of a marked business slowdown/decline The best leading economic indicator I am aware of are the number of homes for sale on my streets in Palm Beach

, Florida and East Hampton, New York. Without fail a rising number of for sale signs presage a business slowdown. And that indicator is now flashing recession, loud and clear. Almost overnight (especially on my street in Palm Beach) and, over the last 12-15 months in East

Hampton, the number of homes for sale have erupted. Already in the Hamptons, prices are falling (hard) and in Palm Beach, price concessions have emerged - as the weakness in the Miami and Ft. Lauderdale markets move in a northerly direction, up the coast of Florida .

These patterns, conform to the multi year weakness that has developed in the high end markets in New York, Los Angeles and other regions - that I have previously discussed in my Diary. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @thedomino @carlquintanilla @beckyquick
